
[1]preservation

   PRESERVA'TION, n. The act of preserving or keeping safe; the act of
   keeping from injury, destruction or decay; as the preservation of life
   or health; the preservation of buildings from fire or decay; the
   preservation of grain from insects; the preservation of fruit or
   plants. When a thing is kept entirely from decay, or nearly in its
   original state, we say it is in a high state of preservation.
